---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Case Study: AlternativaHub | Diogo Soares">
  <article class="py-16">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      {/* Header */}
      <header class="mb-12 max-w-3xl">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <a href="/" class="text-text-muted hover:text-accent transition-colors text-sm flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/><path d="M19 12H5"/></svg>
            <span>Back</span>
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="badge">Product Management</span>
          <span class="badge">LMS</span>
          <span class="badge">Delivery</span>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-text mb-6 leading-tight">
          AlternativaHub – Product Leadership and Delivery for an LMS Platform
        </h1>
        
        <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Democratizing access to knowledge through a robust, flexible, and intuitive infrastructure.
        </p>
      </header>

      {/* Hero Image */}
      <figure class="mb-16 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-card">
        <img 
          src="/images/alternativahub.png" 
          alt="AlternativaHub Interface"
          class="w-full object-cover"
        />
      </figure>

      {/* Content */}
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-custom">
        
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-text mb-4">Overview</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            AlternativaHub was born with the challenge of democratizing access to knowledge through a robust, flexible, and intuitive infrastructure. I acted as <strong class="text-text">Product & Delivery Manager</strong>, leading the complete project lifecycle — from business model definition to platform launch.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-text mb-4">The Challenge</h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The goal was to build a Brazilian learning platform (LMS) that wasn't just a video repository, but a complete education ecosystem. We needed to integrate:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 text-text-secondary mb-6">
            <li><strong class="text-text">Ecommerce:</strong> Course sales with transparent checkout and national payment methods.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">LMS:</strong> Fluid learning experience for students.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Admin:</strong> Simplified administrative panel for educators.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-text">Community:</strong> A native community environment to increase retention and engagement.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-text mb-4">My Role and Methodology</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-text mb-3">1. Strategy and Product Definition</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                I led multidisciplinary squads (Design, Business, and Development) to map personas and the user journey. We identified the pain points of independent educators seeking autonomy from major marketplace platforms. I defined the MVP (Minimum Viable Product), ensuring core payment and content delivery features were solid before expansion.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-text mb-3">2. Open Source Technical Architecture</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                Choosing the <strong class="text-text">WordPress and WooCommerce</strong> ecosystem was strategic. As technical and delivery lead, I focused on scalability (handling access peaks), customization (bespoke UI/UX), and fluid integrations with payment gateways and email marketing.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-text mb-3">3. LMS Experience and Community</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                We implemented specific dashboards for progress tracking and certificate issuance. The key differentiator was <strong class="text-accent">Social Learning</strong>: a native community environment that allowed students and teachers to interact without relying on external groups, keeping focus and data within the ecosystem.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-text mb-4">Results Achieved</h2>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="p-5 bg-surface-subtle rounded-xl border border-border">
              <p class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mb-1">End-to-End</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Record-time launch.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-5 bg-surface-subtle rounded-xl border border-border">
              <p class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mb-1">Autonomy</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Less friction in sales management.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-5 bg-surface-subtle rounded-xl border border-border">
              <p class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mb-1">Engagement</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Higher course completion rate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div class="p-8 bg-surface-elevated rounded-2xl border border-border my-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-display text-text mb-4">Technologies Used</h2>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="badge">WordPress</span>
            <span class="badge">WooCommerce</span>
            <span class="badge">LMS Frameworks</span>
            <span class="badge">PHP</span>
            <span class="badge">Payment APIs</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      {/* CTA */}
      <div class="mt-16 text-center">
        <a href="/#projects" class="btn-accent text-lg px-8 py-4">
          <span>See Other Projects</span>
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
